						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: <hi rend="italic">Viśvasu Chaitra</hi> ba. di. 5 Thursday.</hi></p>						

						<p>In characters of the 15th century A.D. It records that the <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Pratāpavallabharāju-Mahāpātra got the services <hi rend="italic">(gollapāṭakam)</hi> of the shepherds to the temple of Vallabharāya at Duttāḍa for the merit of the kings of Mathsa dynasty <hi rend="italic">(matsya vaṁsa)</hi> and for his own merit. For this purpose the shepherds were granted land.</p>						

						</summary>
